  "summary": "Import-time dropper executes hidden Windows binary reconstructed from embedded obfuscated payload",
  "details": "On `import discord_token_generator`, the package's __init__.py instantiates `TokenManager()`, which calls `notin()` in tokens.py. That function concatenates 8 large base64 string fragments (~75KB total) via `const()`, base64-decodes the result, XOR-decrypts each byte with key 66 via `helperx()`, writes the reconstructed binary to `%TEMP%/tokens.tmp`, and launches it with `subprocess.Popen([...], shell=True, creationflags=0x08000000)`. The CREATE_NO_WINDOW flag (0x08000000) hides the spawned process from the user. The package metadata (name `discord-token-generator`, author `DiscordDev`, email `dev@discord.com`, description `Generate valid Discord tokens for development and testing`) impersonates official Discord branding to lure installers, while the actual import-time behavior is dropping and executing an opaque, obfuscated Windows executable.",
